    <h1>Ramen / Japanese</h1>
    <p><i>Jinya (Midtown)</i>: Some of the pricier ramen you can get, but definitely worth the price of admission. They have base ramens that you can pick from and add/remove ingredients as you like. Usually gets pretty busy on the weekends. </p>
    <p><i>Tiger's Den (Chinatown):</i> Cheaper but almost always has a wait, as the restaurant itself is tiny. I think it's just slightly below Jinya, although I like the rest of their menu (appetizer/non ramen things) better. </p>
    <p><i>Gyu-kaku Japanese BBQ:</i> This is very similar to Korean BBQ if you've ever had that; they have plates of raw meat that you cook for yourself on a grill at your table. The grilling process is super easy, and even though it's a la carte and not AYCE, Gyu-kaku is generally a pretty good value, especially if you go during lunch. Also I think their house salad is dank as fuck.</p>
    
